{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":5,"timestamp":1770048419,"nonce":"8haIB1wAdEYTO445cqeD/zvGmU4=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOQ241x87nqx7mzwAAAAU7WpyC"},"added":["documentation"],"removed":[]},{"type":5,"timestamp":1770048419,"nonce":"/VbH8n+4xMxAGZ0MJmI3IWLlWHk=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOQ241x87nqx7mzwAAAAU7WpzJ"},"added":["enhancement"],"removed":[]},{"type":3,"timestamp":1770048794,"nonce":"ALxdU8AXXRRCLwYS5PJPTVBQz3s=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87kp3QX","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/123#issuecomment-3836179479"},"message":"## Discovery: Issue Number Collision Risk\n\nWhile attempting to use the \"lightweight worktree\" approach (Option 2), identified a critical flaw:\n\n**Problem**: Using \"next available issue number\" for worktree creation risks collision:\n- Agent creates worktree for issue #122 (next available)\n- User/another agent creates real issue #122 for unrelated work\n- Worktree branch `feature/issue-122` now mismatches actual issue #122\n\n**Implication**: Option 2 (lightweight worktree) is **not truly lightweight** if it requires creating a real issue first to avoid collisions.\n\n**Revised Recommendation**:\n\n### Option 2a: Issue-First Worktree (Safe)\n1. Create issue for the fix\n2. Use real issue number: `.agent/scripts/worktree_create.sh --issue \u003cN\u003e --type workspace`\n3. Make changes, commit, push, PR\n4. Clean up worktree\n\n**Still lighter than full workflow**: Skips work plan, draft PR steps\n\n### Option 2b: Branch-Name Worktree (Enhancement Needed)\nSupport creating worktrees without issue numbers:\n```bash\n.agent/scripts/worktree_create.sh --branch fix/description --type workspace\n# Creates: .workspace-worktrees/fix-description/\n```\n\n**Requires**: Script enhancement to support `--branch` parameter without `--issue`\n\n### Testing This Discovery\n\nProceeding with Option 2a (issue-first) to fix the `.gitignore` problem and validate the workflow in practice.\n\n---\n**🤖 Comment-By**: Copilot CLI Agent (Claude Sonnet 4.5)","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1770752709,"nonce":"uBaDuKzjqlkG0OVqp5hMJe5caRI=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87nSRYO","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/123#issuecomment-3880326670"},"message":"Addressed by PR #182: simplified by removing the workflow system — agents now have a script reference table in their framework instruction file.","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1770752710,"nonce":"fKxeHpujFwXDPSB2OU7EWceIWBY=","metadata":{"github-id":"CE_lADOQ241x87nqx7mzwAAAAVIG5Fc"},"status":2}]}